description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Primary Care Network Pharmacist(s)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;Location: Maryport Cumbria &lt;br /&gt;Salary: Competitive&lt;br /&gt;Hours: Part Time/Full Time Hours Considered &lt;br /&gt;Job Type: Permanent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Located in the historic market town of Cockermouth on the edge of the Lake District, we are visionary, forward-thinking and progressive Surgery. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a forward thinking Pharmacist to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team within our surgery with a patient facing role to deliver our Primary Care Network Agenda and Services. You will be or working towards an Independent Prescriber Qualification. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our ethos is building quality of care with a strong emphasis on safety and building a service provision that goes beyond medicine. We are flexible, able to innovate and adapt whilst retaining a good team spirit. We are constantly seeking ways to improve the patient journey and maintain a supportive and motivating culture amongst our staff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an excellent opportunity to join our team and we look forward to meeting you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In summary:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A competitive salary pending experience &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Annual leave: 6 weeks plus bank holiday entitlement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part of the new “Integrated Care Community” with a strategic vision for integrating care services closer to home to suit local needs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Salary pending qualifications &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp; Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Registration with the General Pharmaceutical Council&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Any Additional post graduate clinical qualifications e.g. Certificate (or working towards). Clinical Pharmacy in Pharmacy Practice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Must also be a good communicator and team player&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working patterns will be discussed at interview, additional hours and flexibility will be a requirement of the post to cover annual leave and sickness. For further details see Job Description and Person Specification. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We reserve the right to bring forward the closing date where sufficient applications are received. Short listed applicants will be contacted via email shortly after the closing date. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post-holder will be expected to maintain an active training programme for continuous personal development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would Like to Know More?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please contact the Pharmacy and ask to speak to Rachel Edwards, Prescribing Support Lead, Telephone: 01900 705750&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
